annotation.TEXT: Well... There goes all of my good luck for the day. Now I'm probably going to have horrible luck for the rest of this video. Or, maybe not. I don't know yet.
Well, this room's different... Oh, wait, I think it's actually a horizontal representation of Ludwig's Castle's third room.
And, that would be why I've been colliding with enemies at the top of the screen that I was sure I'd clear with my jumps.
Whoa, parakoopas. Notice how they started off green, and turned red after they lost their wings.
Sure, whatever works.
What? No secret passage here? That's lame! So, once again, we get denied a bonus room in a place where it would belong!
GAH!!! What's going on?! Let me grab the stupid fence!
But this one does!
And of course, watch out for the maces.
Whoa. Yeah, forget this. I'm going to see if the lower route is safer.
No vine? Oh, wait. There it is. Why was it in a different block than expected?
Well, there was a Chuck, but he's no Sumo.
What, Reznor? (Trust me, Reznor is there, even if you can't see them due to the flickering.)
Okay, enough silliness!
To be continued... (I wonder how Wigglers will be implemented, assuming they even show up...)
Man, and here I was thinking that this game was at least being reasonable with the collision detection, but not with parakoopas it seems.
Well, that was dumb. Even dumber, I should've hit midpoint before using my reserve so I'd get a spare mushroom. D'oh.
So, next time, we enter the Forest of Illusion, which has its appropriate music playing on the overworld here. Interesting...
Yep, nothing unusual there. And thus begins Ludwig's Castle...

Yep, totally called it! Because I doubted that the third bridge level would be implemented, nor Soda Lake. (Of course, there was still the possibility of an earlier world's level like Vanilla Secret 2 showing up, but that didn't happen here.)
So, this is... another flower. I'll leave it alone just in case I take a hit in the near future.
BURN! BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! TRI-FORMATION! BURN! WOO! WOO! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! BURN! (Okay, there's my one Flame Hyenard reference for this game.)
No, just six koopas, worth only 200 points apiece.

Wow, this is getting unusually laggy. I think it's because while the ? blocks and "O" blocks are sprites, the brown blocks that appear on failure aren't, which means more total sprites when I'm doing well. Ooh, could I possibly get a perfect?
Also, it's weird how the lava shrunk me first, then I fell through as if it was a bottomless pit. Not that it mattered, as I was equally doomed either way.
Come on. I've managed to build up running speed with much less room than this before.
Huh. It sounded like there was an extra "power up" sound effect there. I think that's because I hit Select before Start at first there.
Have I made it clear how weird the fence physics are in this game yet?
My reason for this is because I was sure I did a cape spin before I took the first hit to those parakoopas, and I want to try cape spinning them again, just to check something.
Okay, so if I'm holding up and right when I hit the left edge of the fence, I'll spaz out and gradually fall off, so make sure to be completely overlapping the fence before trying to climb it.
Perfect. Now, at least these koopas don't have lousy hitboxes.
Okay, seriously. I know I jumped high enough to clear that thing. Is that flower still there, or did it despawn already?

Wow, their hitboxes were bad. Every time I hit the underside of their platforms while big, I took a hit too! (Kind of like how, in the original SMB, if you hit your head on a firebar's hub block while big and not ducking, you get hit for some reason.)
Demo count: 10
Oh, and it even uses the same exit pipe.
Hey, don't you dare stop and stick out your bones at me!
It's way safer, and I can still easily reach the coins... maybe.
Okay, that's good. Now, I think maybe the problem I've been having with high up enemies is that the game is treating my hitbox as not going any higher than a certain point when I jump off screen.
...Assuming I can take off properly...
Oh, and the clouds weren't even that far away. I wonder if I could've reached them with a standard jump. Probably not, due to the horizontal velocity slowing down when jumping normally.
So, to make up for that cheap death, I'm going to grab a mushroom here before resuming that level.
No bonus game in the one pipe that is exit-enabled in the original game. Figures. Hey, does that block happen to have a Yoshi?
Yeah, the maces seem to rotate around smaller circles than in the original game.
Alright, now let's go whale on Ludwig's Castle!
Yep, that totally wor-- ACK!!! Stupid mace!
So, Ludwig got hijacked by Reznor, just like Iggy. I can't see why that would be necessary, but whatever.
I like how my cape spins can take out something that's landing on my head.
And finally, that parakoopa-infested level is done! (Now I'm really glad I didn't get Vanilla Secret 2 instead!)
Alright, it's castle time! Oh, yeah. I think this is the first time I've gotten to a "no-Yoshi" level with Yoshi, so I'll show the whole scene here.
It does! Hi, Yoshi!
Well, that was inter-- Grah!!! I was about to make a comment regarding how that guy looked like a shell-less koopa as the vine was growing, but now I'm kind of annoyed.
Okay, so that new pipe was the exit pipe, and I wasn't ambushed, so that's good.
And it was occupied, but that's not really a problem here.
Even though Yoshi coins are totally worthless, I feel compelled to collect them anyway.
No Sumo Brother?
I was thinking of trying to fly there, but changed my mind.

Wow, another bonus room already? They're sure being spammed lately. Except... I'm not getting anything this time. Either I'm getting exceedingly unlucky, or more likely, it's because I've already done this once already in this level.
Yeah, there's no dangers over here, fortunately. Now, let's go take on Ludwig, with fireballs!
Okay, so if this game's gonna start playing really cheap, so will I! I'm going to farm two feathers here!
Whoa! I didn't mean to drop down yet, but luckily, it was completely safe.
What? Two kicked shells didn't just cancel each other out? What kind of sorcery is this?
Yo, Bony Beetle. You're boned!
Umm... Is it safe to drop down?
Yeah, screw you, Yoshi coin! Whoa, hello there Chuck! I was expecting to see a couple rows of ? blocks before encountering you!
Heck, yeah!!!
Oh, what? Did I get hit simply because I was ascending? And why didn't my cape spin work?
Ooh, will I get to wreck a bunch of moles with this shell?
Bony beetle, eh? Get over here so I can stomp you!
Hello, and welcome back to more Super Mario World, on the NES! So, is this going to be Cookie Mountain? That's my guess, anyway.
Say... Can I spin jump on him to kill him outright just like with Dry Bones?
I do not think I'll be going for all of those coins!
Whoa, okay! Bumping into a wall to the left of the fence causes you to fall suddenly! Now, what's up here?
Actually, you know what? Let's get a feather too.
Not grabbing the mushroom, for obvious reasons.
Oh, no. I am not losing here!
Okay, well there's another fence there.
So, really? Parakoopas are immune to cape spins? That's stupid.
A flower. Hmm... Do I want it? ...Yeah, I'll take it.
I don't remember Ludwig having diagonal podoboos in his castle, though.
Well, the clouds are still up there. I'll see about checking that out later.
Umm... Yeah...
Wow, that was a horrible case of hitbox dissonance...
Oh, that pipe is new. Does it contain another bonus game?
No...
Wow, that was blatantly unfair!
Okay, that 1-up was expected. Now, let's check out those clouds to the left.
Tonight I dine on turtle soup!
Demo count: 11
At least I can spin jump on them just fine, as long as I watch out for their weird hitboxes.
